{
  "stem": "11274.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The cows, everything else, the potatoes in the cellar, everything that we possessed, all the clothes in the wardrobe, everything, jewelry or whatever we had, nothing we could take with us, and to leave the key in the door.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So we left.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I went back one day.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "One day, I went back on foot.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "This was like 20, 30 kilometers.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I went back by foot to ask the sheriff from the town, to risk my life because the Germans were there-- I wasn't supposed to be there-- to ask the sheriff to-- I wore a babushka with the long braids and the clothes like they wear more, not what I was wearing, and ask him if he let me take one cow, because the farm we were living in, we gave him all the money we had.",
      "word_count": 77
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT] And then we had nothing else to buy food or anything.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "So at least we have some milk, that I can have a cow.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "He gave me permission, and he gave me a signed paper that I'm allowed to take the cow, because there were Germans going on trucks and back and forth.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "One of them passing me by said-- they did see.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "I had-- I was wearing the band, then, with the Star of David.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And they said, [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So meaning, we're going to conquer the whole world, and Jerusalem too.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My heart was going like this.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "To-- we'll see you in Jerusalem, he said.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it means they're going to conquer the world.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I just drudged on farther, stopped in one Jewish home on the-- in the halfway, on the way home with this one after this.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they let me keep the cow there overnight, and they gave me some food, and I could sleep there.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
